item.title: New Faces 02 // Photography Journal 47
item.description:
New Faces 02 // Photography Journal 47

In my early photography days I played it safe, taking pictures of buildings and landscapes and simply honing my skills. Over the last few months however I picked up a Canon 7D and a Sigma lens to take some interesting pictures during LCM and LFW for Fucking Young Mag.

item.title: Bologna, Italy // Anton Dee Explores
item.description:
Bologna, Italy // Anton Dee Explores

Every time I visit Italy my train passes Bologna and I just can't help but jump out, even for a couple of hours. Bologna boasts a one of a kind atmosphere that's hard to replicate, even with other Italian cities.

item.title: Rome at Night - A Mindless Wander
item.description:
Rome at Night - A Mindless Wander

Everyone should have a role model, someone whose character and achievements you admire. For me that person is Richard Branson, the founder of Virgin and all round crazy guy who does not like to act his age.

item.title: The Ultimate Aural Orgasm
item.description:
The Ultimate Aural Orgasm

Music really does make the world go round and it would be a pretty grey place without it. I never shy away from trying new things and everyone should give new music genres a go, don't always stick to the tried and tested.

item.title: Exploring EUR - The Dark Side of Rome's Architecture -
item.description:
Exploring EUR - The Dark Side of Rome's Architecture -

Just strolling through Rome left me with an unforgettable experience. When you're surrounded with that much history and culture a little bit of it does rub off on you. When I woke up in my AirBNB apartment on Day 2 I decided to do something different.

item.title: London Collections Men SS17 // Day 3 Street Style
item.description:
London Collections Men SS17 // Day 3 Street Style

As the batteries in my camera and my body were draining LCM Day 3 (View DAY 1 and DAY 2) provided little in way of street style. Rain dampened proceedings but the Meitu #FacesOfFashion team still managed to attend a number of runway shows and presentations.

item.title: Things To Do In London This Summer (Part 1) // Photography Journal 57
item.description:
Things To Do In London This Summer (Part 1) // Photography Journal 57

They say life is short but if you think about it it's actually the longest thing you'll ever get to do. I think what 'they' actually mean is life is too short to spend on things you don't care about.

item.title: Things To Do In London This Summer (Part 2) // Photography Journal 60
item.description:
Things To Do In London This Summer (Part 2) // Photography Journal 60

In the wise words of Mr Fresh Prince "Summer, summer, summertime. Time to sit back and unwind." Lounging by the pool for days on end has never appealed to me though so by unwinding I mean 'get up nice and early and fill your head with information'.

item.title: New Faces 03 // Photography Journal 61
item.description:
New Faces 03 // Photography Journal 61

Reckon I'm going to become a hoarder in my older years as I can't seem to throw anything away. I feel that every photo and screenshot I take needs it's own special folder as it's bound to come in use eventually.
